pageContext.claim: “The great Ed Rollins just said, I just heard it, that never before has a president had to withstand the level of partisan assault from the media that President Trump has had to withstand.”
pageContext.analysis: There's no record of Rollins, a GOP strategist, making these remarks. In a Fox News appearance on Aug. 19, 2018, Rollins said: "No president, no candidate has ever dominated the media, both the cable news, the social media, what have you. He understands it well. His people understand it well." In a 2017 appearance on Fox Business Network, Rollins said the opposite of what Trump is describing: "No president likes their press. To say this is the worst start of any president -- I think Lincoln could make an argument; certainly, Ronald Reagan was shot by this point in time -- you don't get to control the elements that you may want. The media has a job to do; it's not your job, they're not going to do your PR."
